{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-07-02T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today's image takes us to Dungeon Provincial Park on the rugged coast of Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada, where nature tells a much older story. Atlantic waves carved a sea cave with two openings, gradually widening it until the roof gave way. What remains is a striking collapsed formation known as a 'gloup,' surrounded by steep cliffs and crashing surf.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DungeonPark_ROW7201602273_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DungeonPark_ROW7201602273_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Dungeon Provincial Park, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada","Copyright":"© Kaitlyn McLachlan/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260701_DungeonPark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Dungeon+Provincial+Park+Canada&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260701_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260701_DungeonPark"},"Ssd":"20260701","Name":"DungeonPark","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7201602273","FullDateString":"1. jul. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As the sun sinks low in the Masai Mara National Reserve, the silhouettes of Masai giraffes rise against a blazing sky and open plains. Another day comes to an end in the reserve, which stretches across about 1,500 square kilometres in southwestern Kenya, bordering Tanzania's Serengeti National Park. It is a vast expanse, one of the world's greatest wildlife arenas. Rolling grasslands, scattered acacia trees and the life-giving Mara River set the stage for unforgettable encounters.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiGiraffe_ROW6806132366_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiGiraffe_ROW6806132366_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Giraffes at sunset in the Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© danm/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260630_MasaiGiraffe\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Masai+Mara+National+Reserve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260630_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260630_MasaiGiraffe"},"Ssd":"20260630","Name":"MasaiGiraffe","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6806132366","FullDateString":"30. jun. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Beyond its postcard views, Bora Bora has a deeper story to tell. Its lagoon reflects how tropical islands evolve over time. Surrounded by shades of turquoise, this island in French Polynesia is home to one of the South Pacific's most celebrated lagoons, where coral reefs, volcanic peaks and ocean life exist side by side.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BoraBoraLagoon_ROW6505126632_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BoraBoraLagoon_ROW6505126632_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Bora Bora and its lagoon, South Pacific, French Polynesia","Copyright":"© Frederick Millett/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260629_BoraBoraLagoon\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bora+Bora&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260629_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260629_BoraBoraLagoon"},"Ssd":"20260629","Name":"BoraBoraLagoon","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6505126632","FullDateString":"29. jun. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"'Stick around' takes on a new meaning in the Sonoran Desert, where the saguaro cactus has mastered survival. With trunks and arms raised in all directions, this giant has become the American Southwest's mascot.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SaguaroSun_ROW6246109819_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SaguaroSun_ROW6246109819_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Saguaro cacti near Windgate Pass, McDowell Range, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Eric Mischke/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260628_SaguaroSun\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Saguaro+cactus&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260628_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260628_SaguaroSun"},"Ssd":"20260628","Name":"SaguaroSun","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6246109819","FullDateString":"28. jun. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At Boneyard Beach within Hunting Island State Park, South Carolina, United States, the first thing you notice is the trees. Then comes the question: why are bleached trunks and exposed roots scattered across the sand like a scene paused midway through collapse? Since the 1980s, Hunting Island has experienced major beach erosion, with some of the highest rates along the US East Coast—reaching up to 9 metres per year in certain areas.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BoneyardBeach_ROW5980184079_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BoneyardBeach_ROW5980184079_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Driftwood on Boneyard Beach, Hunting Island, South Carolina, USA","Copyright":"© Frances/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260627_BoneyardBeach\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hunting+Island&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260627_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260627_BoneyardBeach"},"Ssd":"20260627","Name":"BoneyardBeach","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5980184079","FullDateString":"27. jun. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What does a parliament, a clock tower and a giant wheel have in common? They all stand beside the River Thames as if London had carefully staged its icons for dramatic effect.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ThamesSummer_ROW5725205310_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ThamesSummer_ROW5725205310_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"The River Thames, London, England","Copyright":"© Daniel Lange/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260626_ThamesSummer\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=River+Thames&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260626_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260626_ThamesSummer"},"Ssd":"20260626","Name":"ThamesSummer","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5725205310","FullDateString":"26. jun. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Few squares in Belgium wear history as well as the Grand Place. The surrounding buildings, seen here, began as guild houses, each funded by a specific trade. Brewers, bakers, merchants and craftsmen treated architecture as language, translating work, status and rivalry into stone through reliefs, coats of arms and generous gold leaf. Styles meet without caution. Gothic verticals rise beside Baroque curves, while the Town Hall, older than its neighbours and unapologetically asymmetrical, holds the composition together.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GrandPlace_ROW9942052634_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GrandPlace_ROW9942052634_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Buildings on Grand-Place Square in Brussels, Belgium","Copyright":"© Vladislav Zolotov/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260625_GrandPlace\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grand+Place+Brussels&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260625_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260625_GrandPlace"},"Ssd":"20260625","Name":"GrandPlace","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9942052634","FullDateString":"25. jun. 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Set in Guatemala's western highlands, Lake Atitlán fills a vast volcanic caldera. Its deep blue waters are framed by steep crater walls and the cone-shaped volcanoes Atitlán, Tolimán and San Pedro. Wooden piers stretch into the still lake, emphasising the contrast between its calm surface and the rugged terrain shaped by volcanic activity.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LakeAtitlan_ROW9281108051_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LakeAtitlan_ROW9281108051_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Sunrise at Lake Atitlán, Guatemala","Copyright":"© shayes17/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260708_LakeAtitlan\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lake+Atitlan+Guatemala&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260708_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260708_LakeAtitlan"},"Ssd":"20260708","Name":"LakeAtitlan","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9281108051","FullDateString":"8. jul. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A bill like a multitool and plumage full of colour—the plate-billed mountain toucan is one of the Andes' most distinctive birds. It lives in the humid mountain forests of Ecuador and southwestern Colombia, perfectly adapted to life high in the canopy.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MountainToucanOrchids_ROW9033619580_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MountainToucanOrchids_ROW9033619580_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Plate-billed mountain toucan with orchids, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Murray Cooper/Minden Pictures","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260707_MountainToucanOrchids\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Plate-billed+mountain+toucan&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260707_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260707_MountainToucanOrchids"},"Ssd":"20260707","Name":"MountainToucanOrchids","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9033619580","FullDateString":"7. jul. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Founded by Greek settlers from Corinth around 734 BCE, the Italian city of Syracuse, on the island of Sicily, grew into one of the ancient Mediterranean's great powers and is now part of a UNESCO World Heritage Site, 'Syracuse and the Rocky Necropolis of Pantalica.' It is forever linked to Archimedes, whose genius still shapes its identity, and to Plato, who came to Syracuse hoping philosophy might shape political life. That layered past still feels tangible at Castello Maniace, a seafront fortress built for Holy Roman Emperor Frederick II in the 13th century, which can still be admired today.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SyracuseItaly_ROW8772538423_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SyracuseItaly_ROW8772538423_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Syracuse at sunset, Sicily, Italy","Copyright":"© Balate Dorin/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260706_SyracuseItaly\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Syracuse+Sicily&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260706_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260706_SyracuseItaly"},"Ssd":"20260706","Name":"SyracuseItaly","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8772538423","FullDateString":"6. jul. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In southeastern France, on the Valensole Plateau, summer arrives in waves of purple and blue. Valensole—one of the largest plateaus in the region—lies in the Verdon Regional Natural Park between the Durance and Asse valleys, near the Gorges du Verdon and its lakes. From mid-June to early July, depending on altitude and weather, lavender and lavandin bloom and transform the landscape into one of Provence's most recognisable sights. The air carries a sharp, dry and unmistakably Mediterranean scent.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LavenderRows_ROW8253115987_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LavenderRows_ROW8253115987_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Lavender rows, Plateau de Valensole, Provence, France","Copyright":"© Robert Harding/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260705_LavenderRows\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lavandula&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260705_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260705_LavenderRows"},"Ssd":"20260705","Name":"LavenderRows","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8253115987","FullDateString":"5. jul. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Tucked between vineyards and mountains, Kaysersberg is one of Alsace's most enchanting villages. Set along the Weiss River in northeastern France, it lies about 12 kilometres northwest of Colmar on the eastern slopes of the Vosges Mountains.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KaysersbergVillage_ROW7990431342_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KaysersbergVillage_ROW7990431342_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Kaysersberg, Alsace, France","Copyright":"© Federica Gentile/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260704_KaysersbergVillage\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Kaysersberg&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260704_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260704_KaysersbergVillage"},"Ssd":"20260704","Name":"KaysersbergVillage","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7990431342","FullDateString":"4. jul. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In Okayama Prefecture, when humid air settles over a stream, hotaru—Japan's fireflies—begin signalling. On warm, windless evenings, they often start glowing about two hours after sunset under favourable conditions, inviting silence beside water.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FirefliesJapan_ROW7733016954_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FirefliesJapan_ROW7733016954_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Fireflies glowing above a stream, Okayama Prefecture, Japan","Copyright":"© tdub303/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260703_FirefliesJapan\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Firefly+insect&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260703_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260703_FirefliesJapan"},"Ssd":"20260703","Name":"FirefliesJapan","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7733016954","FullDateString":"3. jul. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At the Temple of Esna, south of Luxor, Egypt, visitors enter a vivid world devoted to Khnum, the ram-headed god believed to have moulded humanity from Nile clay. Built mainly during the Ptolemaic and Roman eras, the temple's surviving hall is supported by 24 towering columns, each carved with intricate reliefs and ritual texts honouring various deities.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TempleEsna_ROW7472405327_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TempleEsna_ROW7472405327_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Ceiling of the Temple of Esna, Egypt","Copyright":"© Nick Brundle Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260702_TempleEsna\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Temple+of+Esna+Egypt&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260702_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260702_TempleEsna"},"Ssd":"20260702","Name":"TempleEsna","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7472405327","FullDateString":"2. jul. 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Dagens billede","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Få mere at vide","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Doner nu","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Hurtigt faktum:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Seneste startsidebilleder","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Hjemmesidebillede for {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"På denne dag i historien","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"På denne dag i {0}, {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Del dagens startside for Bing","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Download billedet. Dette billede kan kun bruges som baggrundsbillede.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"Download dette billede","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"Dette billede er ikke kan hentes som tapet.","LOC_HOMEPAGE_INFO_TEXT":"Oplysninger","LOC_BING_WP_APP_LINK":"https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linki